24/05/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Ion Iliescu will return to the post of leader of the ruling Social Democratic Party (PSD) after his presidential term expires, party executive president Octav Cozmanca said Sunday (23 May), contradicting rumours that Iliescu would be back as an honorary leader only. Cozmanca added that PSD intends to nominate Prime Minister Adrian Nastase for president in the next election.
In other news, the World Bank announced on Friday that it has approved a $150m loan to Romania to help reduce the country's vulnerability to natural disasters. The loan would be paid back over 17 years, with a five-year grace period. (Mediafax, Rompres, Reuters - 23/05/04)
